tool.command:
@SHELL_OPTIONS@
ln -s '$biom' input.biom &&
echo 'biom.info( biom=input.biom, #if str($label) != '': label=$label, #end if basis=$basis, output=$output, relabund=$relabund, printlevel=$printlevel )' | sed 's/ //g' ## mothur trips over whitespace | mothur | tee mothur.out.log

tool.help:
@MOTHUR_OVERVIEW@
**Command Documentation**
The biom.info command reads a biom file creates a shared file. If your biom file contains metadata mothur will also create taxonomy or constaxonomy along with tax.summary files.
